cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DB

The paper discusses a dual score system for evaluating both researchers and their works, using publication and citation data. This suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL), as well as social networks (cs.SI) and databases (cs.DB) which often involve citation analysis. The mention of author keywords also suggests a potential focus on computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, the paper does not explicitly mention any of these sub-categories, so these are only educated guesses.
